Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 09 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Tendons' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Iliotibial tract' radio button is enabled
And 'Rectus femoris muscle' radio button is enabled
And 'Gluteus minimus muscle' radio button is enabled
And 'Gluteus medius muscle' radio button is enabled

And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled

And 'Rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Tendinopathy' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Right' radio button
Then radio button is selected
When I select 'Left' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I select 'Iliotibial tract' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I select 'Rupture' radio button
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Surrounding hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Proximal' radio button
Then radio button is selected
When I select 'Distal' radio button
Then radio button is selected
When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then  checkbox is selected
And  'Extension' input field is enabled

When I enter '1' in the input field below 'Extension'
Then the number is accepted
When I enter '9999' in the input field below 'Extension'
Then the number is accepted

When I select 'Surrounding hematoma' checkbox
Then  checkbox is selected
When I select 'Bone bruise' checkbox
Then checkbox is selected

When I select 'Tendinopathy' radio button
Then 'Thinning' radio button is selected
And 'Thickening' radio button is selected
And 'Signal increase in PD & T1w' checkbox is selected
And 'Muscle atrophy' checkbox is selected
And 'Ganglion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Thinning' radio button
Then radio button is selected
When I select 'Thickening' radio button
Then radio button is selected
When I select 'Signal increase in PD & T1w' checkbox
Then the checkbox is selected
When I select 'Muscle atrophy'checkbox
Then the checkbox is selected
When I select 'Ganglion' checkbox
Then the checkbox is selected

When I select 'Rupture' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I select 'Rectus femoris muscle' radio button from Localization
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Surrounding hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled
And 'Avulsion tuberosity tibiae' checkbox is enabled

